      "writtenOn": "2019-01-18T21:31:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I personally don\u0027t see the flag itself as a migration strategy. There may be valid reasons why a project in the future is not able to use project scoped accounts.\n\nI think the migration strategy is to go from OPT_IN to OPT_OUT, which will be represented through a change in code behavior if the SecurityOptions is absent. Any other high-level migration controls can be enforced through the config.\n\nNow, if we want to make the migration easier for projects in other timeszones, how about we offer a project_scoped_service_accounts_migrate boolean flag which will control whether we allow a fallback. However I feel that we think too much ahead, since we haven\u0027t explored the actual deployment yet.\n\nRemember that this commit is supposed to unlock dev testing. If it wasn\u0027t a technical necessity, this CL would not be in review yet.",
      "parentUuid": "b601e815_cec99f0f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 76,
        "startChar": 2,
